The paper proposes a real-time end-to-end semantic segmentation method for road-objects based on spherical images transformed from 3D LiDAR point clouds. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and a light-weight network, SqueezeNet, with improvements to balance memory cost and prediction performance. The application of this method is for autonomous driving, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the use of CNNs and deep learning techniques for image processing and segmentation is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training the model on a dataset, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) in the form of text-based label masks, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
